Total hacky prototype at the moment. YYMV.

Currently only builds on mac. For other platforms, the rust-mozjs surgery will need to be duplicated on the appropriate file.

Steps:
* Clone m-c, check out the stylo branch (this one).
* Add this to your .mozconfig:
  ac_add_options --disable-rust
  ac_add_options --enable-macos-target=10.7
* Clone servo, check out the stylo branch.
* Clone https://github.com/bholley/rust-azure, check out the stylo branch.
* Clone https://github.com/bholley/rust-mozjs, check out the stylo branch.
* Set up a .cargo/config override for rust-azure and rust-mozjs.
* Build servo as CEF (./mach build-cef).
* Set up the absolute path in m-c's |toolkit/library/moz.build| to point to your servo build directory.
* Build m-c.
